        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 24 at 5:53PM CDT until June 24 at 6:30PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>SVRSHV

The National Weather Service in Shreveport has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Natchitoches Parish in northwestern Louisiana...
Southeastern Sabine Parish in northwestern Louisiana...

* Until 630 PM CDT.

* At 553 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Kurthwood, or
9 miles north of Slagle, moving northwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Florien, Fisher, Kisatchie, and Mount Carmel.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
